6. Why This Matters for AI

If AI systems become powerful reasoning tools, the safest way to use them is not as a single authority but as a panel of specialized reasoning agents.

Something like:

problem
↓
multiple analytical lenses
↓
conflict between interpretations
↓
human synthesis
↓
decision

This prevents the exact issue you were worried about earlier—blind trust in a single decision engine.

