7. The Interesting Psychological Piece

Humans naturally think through roles and stories better than abstract checklists.

So turning reasoning functions into characters or archetypes (like your Pantheon roles) can actually make complex reasoning easier to manage.

Ancient traditions did this too:
	•	Greek gods represented forces of nature and human traits
	•	medieval councils used symbolic roles
	•	modern organizations still do it with job titles

It’s basically cognitive compression.

